'''''Poor White''''' is an American [[novel]] by [[Sherwood Anderson]], published in 1920.
==Plot introduction== It is the story of an inventor, Hugh McVey, who rises from poverty on the bank of the [[Mississippi River]]. The novel shows the influence of [[industrialism]] on the rural [[:wikt:heartland|heartland]] of America.
